    <statement><div><p>Write the number <m>{500000}</m> in standard form using logarithms.</p>

<p>Express your answer in the form <m>A \times 10^B</m>.</p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>We want to express the number in standard form <m>A \times 10^B</m>.</p>

<p><m>{500000} = {5} \times 10^{5}</m>.</p>

<p>Using logarithms:</p>

<p><me>
\log_{10}({500000}) = \log_{10}({5}) + \log_{10}(10^{5})
</me></p>

<p><me>
= \log_{10}({5}) + {5}.
</me></p>

<p>Therefore the standard form is:</p>

<p><me>
{5} \times 10^{5}.
</me></p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>500000</m></p></answer>
